tags.name: @abstract
tags.description: This member must be implemented (or overridden) by the inheritor.

tags.name: @access
tags.description: Specify the access level of this member (private, public, or protected).

tags.name: @alias
tags.description: Treat a member as if it had a different name.

tags.name: @augments
tags.description: This object adds onto a parent object.

tags.name: @author
tags.description: Identify the author of an item.

tags.name: @borrows
tags.description: This object uses something from another object.

tags.name: @callback
tags.description: Document a callback function.

tags.name: @class
tags.description: This function is intended to be called with the "new" keyword.

tags.name: @classdesc
tags.description: Use the following text to describe the entire class.

tags.name: @constant
tags.description: Document an object as a constant.

tags.name: @constructs
tags.description: This function member will be the constructor for the previous class.

tags.name: @copyright
tags.description: Document some copyright information.

tags.name: @default
tags.description: Document the default value.

tags.name: @deprecated
tags.description: Document that this is no longer the preferred way.

tags.name: @description
tags.description: Describe a symbol.

tags.name: @enum
tags.description: Document a collection of related properties.

tags.name: @event
tags.description: Document an event.

tags.name: @example
tags.description: Provide an example of how to use a documented item.

tags.name: @exports
tags.description: Identify the member that is exported by a JavaScript module.

tags.name: @external
tags.description: Document an external class/namespace/module.

tags.name: @file
tags.description: Describe a file.

tags.name: @fires
tags.description: Describe the events this method may fire.

tags.name: @function
tags.description: Describe a function or method.

tags.name: @global
tags.description: Document a global object.

tags.name: @ignore
tags.description: Omit a symbol from the documentation.

tags.name: @inner
tags.description: Document an inner object.

tags.name: @instance
tags.description: Document an instance member.

tags.name: @kind
tags.description: What kind of symbol is this?

tags.name: @lends
tags.description: Document properties on an object literal as if they belonged to a symbol with a given name.

tags.name: @license
tags.description: Identify the license that applies to this code.

tags.name: @link
tags.syntax:
• {@link someSymbol}
  • {@link http://some.url.com}
  • [caption here]{@link someSymbol}
  • [caption here]{@link http://some.url.com}
  • {@link someSymbol|caption here}
  • {@link http://some.url.com|caption here}
  • {@link http://some.url.com Caption Here (after the first space)}
  • {@link someSymbol Caption Here (after the first space)}
    • The following work in the same way as @link but render in monospace or normal font respectively:
  • {@linkcode ...}
  • {@linkplain ...}
tags.description: Inline tag - create a link.

tags.name: @member
tags.description: Document a member.

tags.name: @memberof
tags.description: This symbol belongs to a parent symbol.

tags.name: @mixes
tags.description: This object mixes in all the members from another object.

tags.name: @mixin
tags.description: Document a mixin object.

tags.name: @module
tags.syntax: @module [[{<type>}] <ModuleName>] Note: If you provide a type, you must also provide a name.`
tags.description: Document a JavaScript module.

tags.name: @name
tags.description: Document the name of an object.

tags.name: @namespace
tags.description: Document a namespace object.

tags.name: @param
tags.description: Document the parameter to a function.

tags.name: @private
tags.description: This symbol is meant to be private.

tags.name: @property
tags.description: Document a property of an object.

tags.name: @protected
tags.description: This member is meant to be protected.

tags.name: @public
tags.description: This symbol is meant to be public.

tags.name: @readonly
tags.description: This symbol is meant to be read-only.

tags.name: @requires
tags.description: This file requires a JavaScript module.

tags.name: @returns
tags.description: Document the return value of a function.

tags.name: @see
tags.description: Refer to some other documentation for more information.

tags.name: @since
tags.description: When was this feature added?

tags.name: @static
tags.description: Document a static member.

tags.name: @summary
tags.description: A shorter version of the full description.

tags.name: @this
tags.description: What does the 'this' keyword refer to here?

tags.name: @throws
tags.description: Describe what errors could be thrown.

tags.name: @todo
tags.description: Document tasks to be completed.

tags.syntax: As a block tag: @tutorial <tutorialID> As an inline tag: {@tutorial <tutorialID>}

tags.description: Document the type of an object.
